      "span_text": "It is possible that the extensive loss of cilia and the slow regeneration of the epithelial surface after bronchiolitis may play a more important role than the slightly diminished CBF in continuing post-bronchiolitis respiratory symptoms. Further studies are required to determine whether RSV infection causes ciliary dyskinesia and, if so, for how long after infection."
